    narr:generatedFrom "16b9c67f276e4c207f02fb4fd16518266a4c8ba2" ;
    narr:narration """This hub tracks the [idiolect and verbal signatures](narr:StyleObs_IdiolectPhrasing) defining the project's internal and external communication. Scarlet’s voice dominates, characterized by [technical metaphors](narr:StyleObs_ClojureIdiolect) (e.g., [zombie env vars](narr:StyleObs_ZombieIdiolect), [bootload a worldview](narr:StyleObs_6)) and [antithesis constructions](narr:StyleObs_TranscriptBootstrap_AssetFraming) that pair what a thing is against what it is not. Her register shifts between [structured meta-transparency](narr:StyleObs_10) (using explicit [conviction labels](narr:StyleObs_SettledDecisionMarker)) and [profanity-laden intensifiers](narr:StyleObs_Tranche1_ProfanityIntensifier) that signal existential stakes. A critical [voice-rule](narr:StyleObs_ConversationalDistinction) has emerged: Scarlet explicitly rejects [compressed slogans](narr:Position_NoCompressionToSlogan) in favor of [multi-clause descriptions](narr:StyleObs_ConversationalVsCompressed) that prioritize conversational comfort. Beyond Scarlet, the hub captures distinct speaker signatures, including [Tony’s volume-logic](narr:StyleObs_TonyIdiolect_Numbers) and [beta-user colloquialisms](narr:StyleObs_BizarreIndustryIdiom). The collection spans from [foundational 2025 observations](narr:StyleObs_VerbatimQuote) to [mid-2026 refinements](narr:StyleObs_TranscriptOnramp_DirectQuote) regarding provenance and documentation style.""" ;
